# Supabase Rules

- Centralize Supabase client creation; do not duplicate client initialization logic.
- Keep auth/session checks on trusted server boundaries for sensitive operations.
- Prefer typed query helpers and explicit column selection.
- Assume RLS is enforced and model access through policy-aware queries.
- Handle expected Supabase errors with clear, user-friendly messages.
- Keep SQL migrations and policy changes reviewed as first-class API changes.
